In a mixing bowl, combine the first eight ingredients and mix well (batter will be thick). Press into an ungreased 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15-20 minutes or until set. Cool for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, combine chocolate chips and peanut butter in a bowl; stir in cornflakes. Carefully spread on top. Cut into bars.